content:
Hi, the `reverse_bit_order(n, order)` of the current specs in https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/specs/das/das-core.md  literally writes the integer `n`  in binary representation, using `log_2(order)` bits, and then reverses this list of bits. 
This does not match with the equally named recursive function in https://hackmd.io/G-Iy5jqyT7CXWEz8Ssos8g that I copy here
```
def reverse_bit_order(bits):
    if bits == 0:
        return [0]
    return (
        [x*2 for x in reverse_bit_order(bits-1)] +
        [x*2+1 for x in reverse_bit_order(bits-1)] 
    )
```
What does this latter one do?
